XPath ka use web elements ko locate karne ke liye hota hai. XPath mainly 2 types ka hota hai:

1️⃣ Absolute XPath
2️⃣ Relative XPath

Difference Between Absolute XPath and Relative XPath
Feature	Absolute XPath	Relative XPath
Path Start	Root node /html se start hota hai	DOM ke kisi bhi element se start ho sakta hai
Syntax	/html/body/div/...	//tag[@attribute='value']
Reliability	Fragile (page structure change hone par break ho jata hai)	Stable aur flexible
Length	Bahut long aur complex hota hai	Short aur readable
Usage	Rarely use hota hai	Mostly automation me use hota hai

-------------------
Absolute XPath
driver.findElement(By.xpath("/html/body/div[1]/form/input[1]"));

➡️ Yeh root se exact path follow karta hai.

Problem:
Agar page me ek extra div add ho gaya, to XPath break ho jayega.

Relative XPath
driver.findElement(By.xpath("//input[@id='username']"));

➡️ Yeh direct element locate karta hai attribute ke basis par.

Isliye automation me mostly relative XPath use hota hai.
--------------------------------------
Absolute XPath starts from the root node of the HTML document and follows the complete path to the element, whereas 
Relative XPath starts from anywhere in the DOM and is more flexible and reliable. In automation, Relative XPath is generally preferred.
